1 the highest bidder for cash. County offices and courts shall be
2 allowed to pass the service fee onto the person requesting to pay
3 via credit card.
4 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
5 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 273 of Title 19, unless there is
6 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
7 All county offices, including courts, shall be responsible for
8 providing any forms necessary to citizens of the county when
9 conducting business or legal proceedings with that county office or
10 court. County offices and courts may not charge a fee for providing
11 or printing such forms. County offices shall make all forms
12 necessary for citizens of the county when conducting business or
13 legal proceedings with that county office or court available on the
14 county website.
15 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 274 of Title 19, unless there is
17 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. Every county office, including the county clerk's office,
19 the county treasurer's office, the county assessor's office, and the
20 county courthouse, shall have a notary available during business
21 hours.
22 B. The notary may not charge a fee for their services.
